oc:kn_10b1962d a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning any email in the lifecycle program" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each email type must map to a specific trigger (time-based, behavior-based, or event-based) and a single primary goal — never create emails without a clear trigger and measurable conversion objective." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Triggerless emails clutter inboxes and degrade engagement. Every email should have a defined entry condition and success metric." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_132c6c50 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing daily/weekly/monthly usage summary emails" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never send an empty usage report — if there is no meaningful activity data, skip the email entirely rather than sending a blank or irrelevant summary." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Empty reports feel automated and impersonal, eroding trust and increasing unsubscribe rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_1435fed7 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing post-purchase onboarding email sequences" ;
    oc:directiveContent "New customer onboarding series should focus on reinforcement and expansion (not conversion) since these users have already committed — differentiate copy from the new user series which targets activation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Treating new paying customers like free trial users feels tone-deaf and misses the opportunity to deepen engagement and reduce early churn." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_7d4d09de a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When starting or reviewing an email program" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the email audit checklist to systematically identify gaps across all six categories (onboarding, retention, billing, usage, win-back, campaigns) before designing new sequences." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Most companies have significant gaps in their lifecycle email coverage — the checklist ensures complete coverage across the customer journey." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_93bba110 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing dunning/failed payment recovery email sequences" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Failed payment recovery sequences must never guilt the customer — assume the failure is accidental (expired card, etc.) and keep the tone clear, direct, and helpful with a single CTA to update payment." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Guilt-based copy damages the relationship and accelerates churn instead of recovering revenue." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

